Recurring Billing Explained
Simple Definition
Recurring billing = automatically charging a customer on a regular schedule (weekly, monthly, yearly) for a subscription or service.
Think: Netflix, Spotify, your gym membership.
How It Works (Step by Step)
Traditional One-Time Payment:
Customer buys something → you charge them once → done
Recurring Billing:
Customer subscribes (agrees to regular charges)
You charge them automatically every month/week/year
Continues until they cancel
Real Examples
Business
